{"type":"message","id":"0affdbec","parentId":"fa344b3c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:59:25.081Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ntbvz1tey9zu_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125813\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 is COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Key finding: CFI Compression Experiment showed CFI�0.7 AND freq<60 is too aggressive\r\n- NEW INSIGHT: Constant Format Problem - tokens like freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n- Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nPending:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n\r\nKey insight: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nSo the next logical step is to implement Strategy C - the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a script or update the experiment to test this scoring formula\r\n2. Run it on the 200 pulses to see if it improves the results\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists. I saw `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` was created. I should check what's there and what needs to be done for the hybrid experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at the pulse script or existing experiment code to understand how to run this. Let me check what files exist.\r\n\r\nSince I need to take a concrete action that advances goals, and the next pending item is the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment, I should:\r\n\r\n1. First understand the existing experiment code\r\n2. Create or modify it to implement Strategy C\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist related to the CFI experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe next logical step per Phase 1 advancement is implementing Strategy C: hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 scoring. The existing experiment showed binary thresholds fail due to the \"constant format problem\" - tokens like \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00) look causal but aren't.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate Strategy C experiment script implementing the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). This tests whether continuous scoring outperforms binary thresholds on the same 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment\r\nGenerated: 2026-03-24\r\nStatus: IMPLEMENTED\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nContinuous scoring: `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)`\r\n- Penalizes constant-format tokens (high freq, high CFI = 1.0 cap)\r\n- Preserves research trajectory tokens (moderate freq, high CFI)\r\n- Avoids binary threshold failure mode\r\n\r\n## Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score | Expected |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|----------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 x 1.0 = 1.00 | HIGH (but should be LOW) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 x 1.0 = 0.96 | MEDIUM |\r\n| \"research trajectory\" | 50 | 0.70 | 0.70 x 0.42 = 0.29 | LOW |\r\n| \"compression\" | 20 | 0.60 | 0.60 x 0.17 = 0.10 | LOW |\r\n| \"? parameter\" | 8 | 0.80 | 0.80 x 0.07 = 0.06 | LOW |\r\n\r\n**Problem**: This formula still scores constant-format tokens too high!\r\n\r\n## Revised Formula\r\nNeed to penalize freq > threshold more aggressively:\r\n\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x (1 - sigmoid((freq - 80) / 20))\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere sigmoid(x) = 1 / (1 + exp(-x))\r\n\r\n| freq | sigmoid penalty | Effective score for CFI=1.0 |\r\n|------|-----------------|----------------------------|\r\n| 20   | 0.001           | 0.999 |\r\n| 60   | 0.14            | 0.86 |\r\n| 80   | 0.50            | 0.50 |\r\n| 100  | 0.88            | 0.12 |\r\n| 120  | 0.98            | 0.02 |\r\n| 160  | 0.9999          | ~0.00 |\r\n\r\nThis properly down-weights constant-format tokens while preserving moderate-frequency research tokens.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nTo be tested against Strategies A (freq-only) and B (CFI-only).\r\nfile: research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_SCORING.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:58:34"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":793,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125813\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 is COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Key finding: CFI Compression Experiment showed CFI�0.7 AND freq<60 is too aggressive\r\n- NEW INSIGHT: Constant Format Problem - tokens like freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n- Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nPending:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n\r\nKey insight: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nSo the next logical step is to implement Strategy C - the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a script or update the experiment to test this scoring formula\r\n2. Run it on the 200 pulses to see if it improves the results\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists. I saw `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` was created. I should check 